sentence.text: In vitro head and neck cancer studies have demonstrated that epidermal growth factor receptor kinase substrate 8 (regulation of cell shape) overexpression contributes to squamous carcinogenesis.
We then correlated our findings with clinicopathologic data including tumor-node-metastasis stage, p16 status, age, multicellular organism development, and smoking and alcohol history.
In conclusion, our data offer in vivo support that, in HNSCCs, regulation of cell shape is involved in tumor invasion but not necessarily the development of regional LN metastasis.
